Introduction

Loossemble was a 5 member South Korean girl group formed by CTDENM. They debuted on September 15th, 2023, with the mini album 'Loossemble'.

The group’s name combines the words “LOONA” and “ASSEMBLE”, reflecting their origin as former popular girl group LOONA members. Loossemble had five members: ViVi, Hyunjin, Go Won, Hyeju, and Yeojin.

In the group's lore, "Loossemble" is also described as the spacecraft the member's board uses to " search for their friends". Their fandom name is "C.Loo", pronounced like "crew", which refers to the spaceship concept, meaning that the fans are the "crew" of the ship.

It was announced on November 29th 2024 that CTD ENM released a statement that the group has reportedly terminated their contract with CTD ENM.
